wiki.content: According to the Hands Songfacts, this was the first song the Ting Tings wrote after an exhausting year and a half on the road, which is reflected when Katie White sings, "clap your hands if you're working too hard." She explained the lyric to Spinner UK: "Traveling around the world, we saw how hard people worked. With our hectic tour schedule, we experienced it first hand. People should have a little more time for themselves." User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.
